article.headline: Central Arkansas 72, Bowling Green 58
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Mitch Rueter had 16 points and four other Central Arkansas players scored in double digits as the Bears beat Bowling Green 72-58 Saturday. Nate Bowie had 15 points, Marcus Pillow 14 and Frederick Campbell 11. Durrell Nevels had 12 points and 12 rebounds for Central Arkansas (4-5). Bowling Green (4-3) led for the last time in the first ten minutes of the game. The Bears led 36-27 at the half and were up by 16 with 13 seconds remaining after going on a 19-5 run. Central Arkansas was 21-of-46 for nearly 46 percent shooting. Bowling Green was 19-for-59 for 32 percent shooting. Martin Samarco led the Falcons with 19 points, and Ryan Sims added 11.
